---
source: examples/hello_world/tests/localised_help.rs
expression: output
---
Friendly greeting demo showcasing OrthoConfig layering

Usage: hello-world [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  greet       Prints a greeting using the configured style
  take-leave  Says goodbye while describing how the farewell will be delivered
  help        Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -c, --config <PATH>
          Path to the configuration file

  -r, --recipient <NAME>
          Recipient of the greeting when supplied on the CLI

  -s, --salutation <WORD>
          Replacement salutations supplied on the CLI

      --is-excited
          Enables an enthusiastic delivery mode from the CLI

      --is-quiet
          Enables a quiet delivery mode from the CLI

  -h, --help
          Print help

  -V, --version
          Print version
